Except your example for `DoStuff(a++)` is wrong. It should be:

    int temp = a;
    a = a + 1;
    DoStuff(temp);

Additionally, his example is wrong. I'm not amazed how often people don't quite understand post-increment (variable++), but I see it wrong almost every time. Post-increment does not evaluate after the call. It evaluates before the call, specifically:

int temp = a;
a = a + 1;
DoStuff(temp);
